The paper focuses on neural architecture search for image restoration tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of evolutionary search also suggests a potential overlap with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the optimization of neural network hyperparameters, which is a common topic in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves the ImageNet dataset, which is commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) research.
